  <keyword>interp3</keyword>
  <short_description>Interpolation for 3-D gridded data in meshgrid format</short_description>
  <syntax>
    <syntax_item>Vq = interp3(X, Y, Z, V, Xq, Yq, Zq)</syntax_item>
    <syntax_item>Vq = interp3(V, Xq, Yq, Zq)</syntax_item>
    <syntax_item>Vq = interp3(V)</syntax_item>
    <syntax_item>Vq = interp3(V, k)</syntax_item>
    <syntax_item>Vq = interp3(..., method)</syntax_item>
    <syntax_item>Vq = interp3(..., method, extrapval)</syntax_item>
  </syntax>
  <param_input>
    <param_input_item>
      <param_name>X, Y, Z</param_name>
      <param_description>Sample grid points: vectors or meshgrid arrays.</param_description>
    </param_input_item>
    <param_input_item>
      <param_name>V</param_name>
      <param_description>Sample values: real or complex 3-D array.</param_description>
    </param_input_item>
    <param_input_item>
      <param_name>Xq, Yq, Zq</param_name>
      <param_description>Query points.</param_description>
    </param_input_item>
    <param_input_item>
      <param_name>method</param_name>
      <param_description>
        &apos;linear&apos;, &apos;nearest&apos;, &apos;cubic&apos;, &apos;makima&apos;, or &apos;spline&apos;.</param_description>
    </param_input_item>
  </param_input>
  <param_output>
    <param_output_item>
      <param_name>Vq</param_name>
      <param_description>Interpolated values.</param_description>
    </param_output_item>
  </param_output>
  <description>
    <p>
      <b>interp3</b> interpolates 3-D gridded data using meshgrid conventions. The default grid is X=1:size(V,2), Y=1:size(V,1), Z=1:size(V,3).</p>
    <p>The cubic-family methods use a native tensor-product four-point stencil, with linear fallback on dimensions that have fewer than four samples.</p>
    <p>
      <b>interp3(V)</b> and <b>interp3(V,k)</b> refine the default grid. Grid vectors must be strictly monotonic.</p>
  </description>
  <examples>
    <example_item>
      <example_item_type>nelson</example_item_type>
      <example_item_description />
      <example_item_data><![CDATA[V = reshape(1:8, [2 2 2]);
Vq = interp3(V, 1.5, 1.5, 1.5)]]></example_item_data>
    </example_item>
    <example_item>
      <example_item_type>nelson</example_item_type>
      <example_item_description />
      <example_item_data><![CDATA[V = reshape(1:8, [2 2 2]);
Vq = interp3(V, 1)]]></example_item_data>
    </example_item>
    <example_item>
      <example_item_type>nelson</example_item_type>
      <example_item_description />
      <example_item_data><![CDATA[x = 1:2;
y = 1:2;
z = 1:2;
[X,Y,Z] = meshgrid(x, y, z);
V = reshape(1:8, [2 2 2]);
Vq = interp3(X, Y, Z, V, 1.5, 1.5, 1.5, 'linear')]]></example_item_data>
    </example_item>
    <example_item>
      <example_item_type>nelson</example_item_type>
      <example_item_description />
      <example_item_data><![CDATA[V = reshape(1:8, [2 2 2]);
Vq = interp3(V, 0, 1.5, 1.5, 'linear', -1)]]></example_item_data>
    </example_item>
  </examples>
